# Development Roadmap

Phase 1: Foundation Setup (Days 1-2)

- [x] Initialize project and install dependencies
- [x] Configure environment variables
- [x] Set up Express app with basic middleware
- [x] Connect to Database
- [x] Create base error handling structure
- [x] Set up nodemon and development scripts

Key Concepts: Project initialization, middleware chain, environment management

Phase 2: Authentication System (Days 3-5)

 Design User model (email, password, roles, profile)
 Implement password hashing with bcrypt
 Build registration endpoint with validation
 Create login with JWT access & refresh tokens
 Build email verification flow
 Implement password reset functionality
 Create auth middleware for protected routes
 Add logout and token refresh endpoints

Key Concepts: JWT authentication, password security, token management, email verification

Phase 3: User Management (Days 6-7)

 Get user profile endpoint
 Update user profile (name, bio, etc.)
 Upload avatar with Multer + Cloudinary
 Change password endpoint
 Search users functionality
 User activity logs

Key Concepts: File upload, cloud storage integration, profile management

Phase 4: Team Management (Days 8-10)

 Design Team model (name, owner, members with roles)
 Create team endpoint
 Invite users to team (generate invitation tokens)
 Accept/decline team invitations
 Update team details
 Remove members from team
 Role-based permissions (owner, admin, member)
 Leave team functionality

Key Concepts: Many-to-many relationships, role-based access control, invitation system

Phase 5: Project Management (Days 11-13)

 Design Project model (linked to team, with members)
 Create project within a team
 Assign team members to projects
 Update project details
 Archive/delete projects
 Get all projects (with filtering and pagination)
 Project permissions (who can view/edit)

Key Concepts: Nested resources, authorization logic, pagination, filtering

Phase 6: Task Management (Days 14-17)

 Design Task model (title, description, assignees, priority, status, due date)
 Create task within a project
 Assign task to users
 Update task details
 Change task status (todo, in-progress, completed)
 Set priority and due dates
 Delete tasks
 Get tasks with advanced filters (status, priority, assignee, date range)
 Task sorting and pagination

Key Concepts: Complex filtering, date handling, status management

Phase 7: Comments & Attachments (Days 18-19)

 Design Comment model
 Add comments to tasks
 Edit/delete comments
 Upload file attachments to tasks
 Download/delete attachments
 Comment notifications

Key Concepts: Nested documents vs references, file management, notifications

Phase 8: Activity Logging & Notifications (Days 20-21)

 Design ActivityLog model
 Log all major actions (task created, assigned, completed, etc.)
 Get activity feed for projects/teams
 In-app notification system
 Mark notifications as read
 Email notifications for key events

Key Concepts: Audit trails, event tracking, notification patterns

Phase 9: Advanced Features (Days 22-24)

 Search functionality (tasks, projects, users)
 Dashboard statistics (tasks completed, overdue, etc.)
 Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints
 Request validation refinement
 Soft delete implementation
 API response standardization

Key Concepts: Aggregation pipelines, analytics, security hardening

Phase 10: Testing & Documentation (Days 25-27)

 Write unit tests for services
 Write integration tests for API endpoints
 Create API documentation with Swagger
 Add comprehensive error messages
 Performance optimization
 Security audit

Key Concepts: Testing strategies, API documentation, optimization